{"questionId":"15470010","questionHtml":"<p>Hence. show that&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>sin</mi><mfrac><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><mn>5</mn></mfrac><mi>sin</mi><mfrac><mrow><mn>3</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi></mrow><mn>5</mn></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><msqrt><mn>5</mn></msqrt><mn>4</mn></mfrac></math></p>","markschemeHtml":"<p><strong>METHOD 1</strong></p>\n<p>attempt to use quadratic formula:&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>&nbsp;(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><em><strong><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>sin</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mi>θ</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>20</mn><mo>±</mo><msqrt><mn>80</mn></msqrt></mrow><mn>32</mn></mfrac></math>&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><em><strong><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>5</mn><mo>±</mo><msqrt><mn>5</mn></msqrt></mrow><mn>8</mn></mfrac></math></strong></em></p>\n<p><em><strong><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>sin</mi><mo> </mo><mi>θ</mi><mo>=</mo><msqrt><mfrac><mrow><mn>5</mn><mo>±</mo><msqrt><mn>5</mn></msqrt></mrow><mn>8</mn></mfrac></msqrt></math></strong></em></p>\n<p><em><strong><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>⇒</mo><mi>sin</mi><mfrac><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><mn>5</mn></mfrac><mi>sin</mi><mfrac><mrow><mn>3</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi></mrow><mn>5</mn></mfrac><mo>=</mo><msqrt><mfrac><mrow><mn>5</mn><mo>+</mo><msqrt><mn>5</mn></msqrt></mrow><mn>8</mn></mfrac></msqrt><msqrt><mfrac><mrow><mn>5</mn><mo>-</mo><msqrt><mn>5</mn></msqrt></mrow><mn>8</mn></mfrac></msqrt></math>&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;M1</strong></em></p>\n<p><em><strong><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><msqrt><mfrac><mn>20</mn><mn>64</mn></mfrac></msqrt></math>&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><em><strong><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><msqrt><mfrac><mn>5</mn><mn>4</mn></mfrac></msqrt></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;AG</strong></em></p>\n<p><em><strong>&nbsp;</strong></em></p>\n<p><strong>METHOD 2</strong></p>\n<p>roots of quartic are&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>sin</mi><mfrac><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><mn>5</mn></mfrac><mo>,</mo><mi>sin</mi><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi></mrow><mn>5</mn></mfrac><mo>,</mo><mi>sin</mi><mfrac><mrow><mn>3</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi></mrow><mn>5</mn></mfrac><mo>,</mo><mi>sin</mi><mfrac><mrow><mn>4</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi></mrow><mn>5</mn></mfrac></math>&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>attempt to set product of roots equal to&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>±</mo><mfrac><mn>5</mn><mn>16</mn></mfrac></math>&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>M1</strong></em></p>\n<p><em><strong><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>sin</mi><mfrac><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><mn>5</mn></mfrac><mi>sin</mi><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi></mrow><mn>5</mn></mfrac><mi>sin</mi><mfrac><mrow><mn>3</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi></mrow><mn>5</mn></mfrac><mi>sin</mi><mfrac><mn>4</mn><mn>5</mn></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>5</mn><mn>16</mn></mfrac></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>recognition that&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>sin</mi><mfrac><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><mn>5</mn></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mi>sin</mi><mfrac><mrow><mn>4</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi></mrow><mn>5</mn></mfrac></math>and&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>sin</mi><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi></mrow><mn>5</mn></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mi>sin</mi><mfrac><mrow><mn>3</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi></mrow><mn>5</mn></mfrac></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>sin</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mfrac><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><mn>5</mn></mfrac><msup><mi>sin</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mfrac><mrow><mn>3</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi></mrow><mn>5</mn></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>5</mn><mn>16</mn></mfrac></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong> A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><em><strong><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>sin</mi><mfrac><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><mn>5</mn></mfrac><mi>sin</mi><mfrac><mrow><mn>3</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi></mrow><mn>5</mn></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><msqrt><mn>5</mn></msqrt><mn>4</mn></mfrac></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; AG</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>METHOD 3</strong></p>\n<p>Consider&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>16</mn><mo> </mo><msup><mi>sin</mi><mn>4</mn></msup><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>θ</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>20</mn><mo> </mo><msup><mi>sin</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mi>θ</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>5</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math>&nbsp;as a quadratic in&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>sin</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>θ</mi></math>&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>M1</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><mi>θ</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><mn>5</mn></mfrac><mo>,</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>3</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi></mrow><mn>5</mn></mfrac><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mtext>are&nbsp;roots</mtext></mrow></mfenced></math>, so&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>sin</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mfrac><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><mn>5</mn></mfrac></math>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>sin</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mfrac><mrow><mn>3</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi></mrow><mn>5</mn></mfrac></math>are roots of the quadratic.&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>Consider product of roots:&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>&nbsp;M1</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>⇒</mo><msup><mi>sin</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfrac><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><mn>5</mn></mfrac><msup><mi>sin</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mfrac><mrow><mn>3</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi></mrow><mn>5</mn></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>5</mn><mn>16</mn></mfrac></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>&nbsp; A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>sin</mi><mfrac><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><mn>5</mn></mfrac><mi>sin</mi><mfrac><mrow><mn>3</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi></mrow><mn>5</mn></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><msqrt><mn>5</mn></msqrt><mn>4</mn></mfrac></math>&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>&nbsp;AG</strong></em></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:right;\"><em><strong>[4 marks]</strong></em>&nbsp;</p>","meta":{"questionId":"15470010","referenceCode":"23N.1.AHL.TZ2.12cii","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"Hence. show that sinπ5sin3π5=54","paper":"1","level":"HL","questionNumber":"ii","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 4]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 1—Number and algebra","Topic 2—Functions","Topic 2—Functions","AHL 2.12—Factor and remainder theorems, sum and product of roots","Topic 1—Number and algebra","AHL 1.13—Polar and Euler form","Topic 1—Number and algebra","AHL 1.14—Complex roots of polynomials, conjugate roots, De Moivre’s, powers & roots of complex numbers"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}